Your configuration are creating two DataSource beans. Your entity manager doesn&#39;t know which one to use.
If you want to use both connections in your application, try to name your bean and use @Qualifer in your entity manager to pick the right data source to use.
```
    @Bean
    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix=&quot;spring.datasource&quot;)
    public DataSource primaryDataSource() {
        return DataSourceBuilder.create().build();
    }

    @Bean(name=&quot;secondaryDS&quot;)
    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix=&quot;spring.SecondDatasource&quot;)
    public DataSource secondaryDataSource() {
        return DataSourceBuilder.create().build();
    }
```
On the other hand, if you are trying to configure a fallback connection, you need to use something like @ConditionOnProperty to support your @Primary annotation, for example
```
    @Bean
    @Primary
    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix=&quot;spring.datasource&quot;)
    @ConditionalOnProperty(name=&quot;spring.datasource.url&quot;)
    public DataSource primaryDataSource() {
        return DataSourceBuilder.create().build();
    }

    @Bean
    @ConfigurationProperties(prefix=&quot;spring.SecondDatasource&quot;)
    @ConditionalOnMissingBean
    public DataSource secondaryDataSource() {
        return DataSourceBuilder.create().build();
    }
```

