Consolidating the bytes into a byte array will cause a bottleneck as you are not trying to hold the entire stream in-memory which can easily run into OutOfMemory problems with large streams.  Instead, you&#39;ll want to pipeline the bytes through all the IOStreams like above.

I created a Java library that does this for you https://github.com/spoorn/tar-lz4-java.

If you want to implement it yourself, here&#39;s a technical doc that includes details on how to LZ4 compress a directory using TarArchive from Apache Commons and lz4-java: https://github.com/spoorn/tar-lz4-java/blob/main/SUMMARY.md#lz4

